result.execSummary:
The defendant Jared Lee Emerson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event that the defendant is discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent SHALL notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment SHALL be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

miscConds.notes: Defendant to pay court costs and DNA surcharge.  Cash bond to be applied, balance to be refunded to poster.
Defendant is to comply with any treatment/programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment, agent, and treatment court.

timeConds.notes: Last 6 months stayed pending participation and successful completion of Trempealeau County Recovery Court.  Defendant eligible for Huber to attend medical appointments, counselling appointments, and any Recovery Court recommended treatment.  Defendant may use Huber to work for his father on farm.  Father must verify hours and must sign off on a daily time card.  Defendant may use 1 day of Huber for appointment with Department of Motor Vehicles.  7 days jail credit to be applied to first 3 months of sentence.  Defendant is to report to Trempealeau County Jail on 01-06-2017 by 6:00 pm.
